.TH "doc_read_data_area" 9 "doc_read_data_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
doc_read_data_area \- Read data from data area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" doc_read_data_area
.BI "(struct docg3 *docg3 "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int first "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "docg3" 12
the device
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer to fill in (might be NULL is dummy reads)
.IP "len" 12
the length to read
.IP "first" 12
first time read, DOC_READADDRESS should be set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads bytes from flash data. Handles the single byte / even bytes reads.
